---
import SiteLayout from "../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
---

<SiteLayout
	title="Aoi Tsukikage Engineering"
	description="Portfolio section scaffold for the first-pass four-page information architecture."
	currentPath={Astro.url.pathname}
>
	<div class="page-stack">
		<section class="shell section-card" id="home-hero">
			<div class="hero-copy">
				<p class="section-kicker">[SYSTEM] home.hero</p>
				<h1>Placeholder hero copy defines the first impression layer for the portfolio.</h1>
				<p class="summary">
					This pass only maps section order, CTA hierarchy, and placeholder content
					for the four-page launch shell.
				</p>
				<div class="meta-row">
					<span class="meta-chip">Hero Tier 01</span>
					<span class="meta-chip">Primary CTA Map</span>
					<span class="meta-chip">Placeholder Only</span>
				</div>
				<div class="cta-row">
					<a class="cta-link" href="/projects">View Projects</a>
					<a class="cta-link secondary" href="/contact">Contact</a>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="hero-panel">
				<p class="section-tag">[MISSION] hero-support</p>
				<p class="section-anchor">section/home/hero-support</p>
				<p>
					Support panel reserved for concise status, working mode, or route context
					without introducing final biography or project details.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="section-card section-shell" id="home-intro">
			<p class="section-kicker">[SYSTEM] home.intro</p>
			<p class="section-anchor">section/home/intro</p>
			<h2>Intro section placeholder frames the site intent in one compact block.</h2>
			<p>
				Placeholder copy for the homepage overview. Final narrative, proof points,
				and resume-level detail remain deferred.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="section-card section-shell" id="home-focus-areas">
			<p class="section-kicker">[SYSTEM] home.focus-areas</p>
			<p class="section-anchor">section/home/focus-areas</p>
			<h2>Focus areas section marks where three domain signals will be introduced.</h2>
			<div class="section-grid">
				<article class="section-card">
					<p class="section-tag">[MISSION] focus-card-01</p>
					<h3>Placeholder focus area one</h3>
					<p>Reserved for short summary text and one future directional cue.</p>
				</article>
				<article class="section-card">
					<p class="section-tag">[MISSION] focus-card-02</p>
					<h3>Placeholder focus area two</h3>
					<p>Reserved for short summary text and one future directional cue.</p>
				</article>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="section-card section-shell" id="home-featured-pointer">
			<p class="section-kicker">[SYSTEM] home.featured-pointer</p>
			<p class="section-anchor">section/home/featured-pointer</p>
			<h2>Featured pointer section reserves space for one highlighted route into Projects.</h2>
			<p>
				Only the pointer structure exists here. No project taxonomy, content entry,
				or detail page is introduced in this pass.
			</p>
			<div class="cta-row">
				<a class="cta-link" href="/projects">Open Projects Hub</a>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="section-card section-shell" id="home-cta">
			<p class="section-kicker">[SYSTEM] home.cta-band</p>
			<p class="section-anchor">section/home/cta-band</p>
			<h2>Final homepage CTA band keeps the exit routes explicit.</h2>
			<p>Placeholder CTA copy for the next action layer after the homepage scan.</p>
			<div class="cta-row">
				<a class="cta-link" href="/about">Read About</a>
				<a class="cta-link secondary" href="/contact">Start Contact Route</a>
			</div>
		</section>
	</div>
</SiteLayout>

<style>
	.shell {
		display: grid;
		gap: 2rem;
		grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.6fr) minmax(18rem, 0.9fr);
		place-items: start;
	}

	.hero-copy {
		display: grid;
		gap: 1rem;
		max-width: 42rem;
	}

	h1 {
		font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 7vw, 4.5rem);
	}

	.hero-panel {
		background: rgba(120, 192, 255, 0.08);
		border: 1px solid rgba(120, 192, 255, 0.2);
		min-height: 100%;
	}

	.summary {
		font-size: 1.1rem;
	}

	@media (max-width: 900px) {
		.shell {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
	}
</style>
